EWG Supporter Comments on the EPA’s Proposed Interim Registration Review Decision for Glyphosate
September 3, 2019
To: Office of Pesticide Programs Environmental Protection Agency 1200 Pennsylvania Avenue, N.W. Washington, D.C. 20004
Submitted electronically to docket EPA-HQ-OPP-2009-0361-2340
The undersigned 79,537 supporters of Environmental Working Group (EWG) object to the Environmental Protection Agency’s proposed decision on glyphosate. The EPA’s decision disregards the cancer risks and children’s health risks posed by glyphosate.
79,537 supporters signed EWG’s petition stating: Monsanto's glyphosate is NOT safe!
This cancer-linked chemical shouldn't be anywhere near our food, parks or schools. I urge you to listen to independent research – not Monsanto's propaganda – and take action to protect Americans from glyphosate's carcinogenic risks.
EWG and our supporters urge you to take steps to protect Americans, especially children, from glyphosate exposure.
Sincerely,
